-- Canon to suspend operations at three plants in China-Japan media
-- 
-- Sun Sep 16, 2012 11:54pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/09/17/us-china-japan-canon-idUSBRE88G03I20120917

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japanese electronics maker Canon Inc ( 7751.T ) is set to suspend operations at three of its four plants in China on Monday and Tuesday following huge anti-Japanese protests in China, Japanese media reported on Monday. 
 Canon will halt production lines at its laser printer factory in Guangdong, a digital camera factory in Guangdong, and a copier plant in Jiangsu, Japanese media reported. (Reporting by  Yoko Kubota ; Editing by  Paul Tait )